webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Portrait of painting master Anders Thorselius. Moving to Lköpping in 1808 to settle and run a workshop in the new city’s Tannefors block No. 11, within the present block Dyaren. Unclear if he moved from Klockrike or Stockholm. Both localities are mentioned in the sources. Whatever he was left at the address of his death in 1853. At the time, he had long served as the alderman of the crow. The painter remained unmarried through life - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMEA0001240106. (en) Brandseph. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021017742560. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
